.TH "tpm2_shutdown" 9 "tpm2_shutdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm2_shutdown \- send a TPM shutdown command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tpm2_shutdown
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u16 shutdown_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
a \fItpm_chip\fP instance
.IP "shutdown_type" 12
TPM_SU_CLEAR or TPM_SU_STATE.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Sends a TPM shutdown command. The shutdown command is used in call
sites where the system is going down. If it fails, there is not much
that can be done except print an error message.
